The paper deals with a communication channel model and its capacity regions, which are topics typically studied in the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category. The channel model involves two transmitters, which suggests the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-category. The concept of cognitive communication is also relevant to the Signal Processing (cs.SP) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the difference between message side-information and codeword side-information, which relates to the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories.
